{
  "stem": "25639.3",
  "chunk_idx": 7,
  "model": "openai/gpt-oss-120b",
  "elapsed_s": 11.9,
  "sentences_input": [
    {
      "segment_idx": 7,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 8,
      "text": "[PAUSES FOR 3 SECONDS] Every morning, as we would march to work at 7:00 AM, we would always see human beings against the electric wire fences, like that.",
      "word_count": 28
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 7,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 9,
      "text": "These people had actually committed suicide.",
      "word_count": 6
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 7,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 10,
      "text": "All of us lost members from our families and most of us lost everyone, so naturally, we were quite sad.",
      "word_count": 20
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 7,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 11,
      "text": "[PAUSES FOR 5 SECONDS] We didn't really know, for a few days, where we were.",
      "word_count": 15
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 7,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 12,
      "text": "We had no idea that there was such a thing as a death camp.",
      "word_count": 14
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 7,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 13,
      "text": "We had no idea that human beings are exterminated like cattle-- not even that humanely-- on a mass basis.",
      "word_count": 19
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 7,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 14,
      "text": "I'll give you-- I'll draw a little picture [PAUSES FOR 3 SECONDS] as to how I came to this realization.",
      "word_count": 20
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 7,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 15,
      "text": "The first three days or so, we were in a special barracks after we arrived.",
      "word_count": 15
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 7,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 16,
      "text": "After the dehumanization process of shaving the head and tattooing us and receiving gray cotton uniforms, which were really much like rags, [PAUSES FOR 3 SECONDS] we were placed in this, these barracks where they were supposed to apparently make sure that we don't, didn't come with any contagious diseases.",
      "word_count": 50
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 7,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 17,
      "text": "In a death camp, mind you, that we didn't come with any, any contagious diseases and infect them, perhaps.",
      "word_count": 19
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 8,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "We just liked to sing, and how nice it would be to sing for the old timers.",
      "word_count": 17
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 8,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "And these were the Jews from Czechoslovakia, Germany, Austria, France, Poland, Germany, and so on.",
      "word_count": 15
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 8,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "And so we decided to, to pick 'Hatikvah.' We all knew the melody to 'Hatikvah.' And we didn't know the words in Hebrew yet to 'Hatikvah,' but we knew it-- we knew the words to it in Hungarian.",
      "word_count": 38
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 8,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 3,
      "text": "[PAUSES FOR 4 SECONDS] I remember knowing it in Czech, too, but I can't remember the words in Czech anymore.",
      "word_count": 20
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 8,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 4,
      "text": "[PAUSES FOR 3 SECONDS]",
      "word_count": 4
    }
  ],
